<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en-us" lang="en-us">
  <% bot = Config['irc']['nick'] %>
  <head>
    <title>Alfred the IRC butler</title>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
    <link href="/css/master.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    
    <script type="text/javascript" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.3.2/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/jquery.tweetable.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">
      $(document).ready(function() {
        $('#latest-tweets').tweetable({username: '<%= bot %>', time: false, limit: 1});
      });
    </script>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="page">
      <div id="header">
        <h1><%= bot %> gladly serving <em>#<%= Config['irc']['channel'] %></em></h1>
        <a href="http://quasipartikel.at/"><span>quasipartikel.at</span></a>
      </div>

      <div id="content">
        <div id="sidebar">
          <div id="twitter">
            <a class="twitter-follow" href="http://twitter.com/<%= bot %>">follow me on twitter</a>
            <div id="latest-tweets"></div>
          </div>
          <h2>find</h2>
          <ul id="menu">
            <li><a href="/tags">tags</a></li>
            <li><a href="/people">people</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts">all posts</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts?type=documentation">documentation</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts?type=question">questions</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts?type=reply">replies</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts?type=note">notes</a></li>
            <li><a href="/commands">commands</a></li>
          </ul>
          <h2>about</h2>
          <p>
            <em><%= bot %></em> can help you collect useful information from irc channels.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can store away posts so that you can use them later on when you're writing
            your project's documentation, wiki pages, blog articles or whatever. You can tag
            these posts so that they are easier to find later on.
          </p>
          <p>
            Of course you're not limited to posting snippets of text. Just post a link to <em><%= bot %></em>,
            say to a <a href="http://pastie.org">pastie</a>, a <a href="http://gist.github.com">gist</a>
            or some interesting blogpost and tag them as you wish. <em><%= bot %></em> has convenient
            <a href="/commands">commands</a> to retrieve them later on.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can use <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax">Markdown</a>
            for basic formatting of your messages. Use this especially for links, so that <em><%= bot %></em>
            can correctly format them on the website.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div id="main">
          <%= yield %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="footer">
        <p>
          a <a href="http://quasipartikel.at">quasipartikel</a> production
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
